{
  "texts": [
    "Fine-tuning has been proposed to address this (Subramanian et al., 2023), but often requires substantial data per new PDE instance (Herde et al., 2024; Hao et al., 2024).",
    "To improve generalization, several methods train across multiple PDE environments.",
    "LEADS(Yin et al., 2022a) employs a shared model with environment-specific modules, updated during inference.",
    "Similarly, Kirchmeyer et al. (2022) introduce a hypernetwork conditioned on learnable context vectors c e, enabling adaptation to new environments.",
    "Building on this, NCF(Nzoyem et al., 2025) uses a Taylor expansion to dynamically adjust context vectors, offering both uncertainty estimation and inter-environment adaptation."
  ]
}